About
=====
A dynamic-link library version for MSVC is available. You can use it to communicate with services running on Apple iPhone/iPod Touch devices. You can find the source code here http://www.libimobiledevice.org/. And there is a list about what this library support. I just compiled it on Windows, so you can use it in your win32 apps.

Requirements
============
  MSVC
  iTunes Installed & AppleMobileDevice Service Started

Usage
=====================
Create a new Project.Set include directory and libs properly. (http://www.bingtech.net/wordpress/2011/03/189/)

Tips: More codes and API documents you can find at http://www.libimobiledevice.org/.
Notice: Maybe u need glib2 or gnutls libs which u can find by google.

